<h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 32.1 (July 17th, 2014)</h4><ul><li>Base health reduced to 525, down from 540.</li><li>Health per level reduced to 78, down from 84.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 32 (July 9th, 2014)</h4><ul><li><b>Snapdragon (Q)</b></li><ul><li>Fixed a bug where this ability would execute an auto attack immediately after landing instead of waiting for the 0.2 second intended delay.</li><li>Fixed a bug where the first auto attack executed after this ability connected would always be a guaranteed hit, regardless of the target's distance.</li></ul><li><B>Bramblecrush (E)</B></li><ul><li>The base damage of this ability has been reduced to 60/100/140/180/220, down from 60/105/150/195/240.</li></ul><li><b>Force of Nature (R)</b></li><ul><li>The bonus Health gained from activating this ability has been reduced to 150/275/400, down from 150/300/450.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 26 (Feb 24, 2014)</h4><ul><li>Circle of Life (Passive)</li><ul><li>The radius in which seeds will spawn has been increased by 30%.</li><li>The radius in which Marah may pick up the seed has been increased by 80%.</li><li>Seeds will now have a minimum value of 0.5 Health per seed after reaching 80 stacks.</li><li>The maximum seeds you may collect has been increased to 9999, up from 400.</li></ul><li>Snapdragon (Q)</li><ul><li>The projectile width of this ability has been widened by 50%.</li><li>Fixed a bug that would cause Marah to not get pulled to her target if the target dispelled the effect.</li><li>Fixed a bug that would cause Marah to not get pulled to her target if she was silenced during the effect.</li></ul></ul>